result.execSummary:
Bryant Killebrew was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Bryant Killebrew was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle. ADA:   Edward Minser   DF ATTY:  Daniel James Chapman   DF:  Bryant Killebrew appeared from jail. Case called at 1:02 p.m. Court reviews file. ADA Minser State's Exhibit #1(governors warrant). Atty Chapman does have a copy as well. His client does not want to waive extradition and would like to continue with hearing. ADA Minser calls Mark Mehl to the stand. S/T Mark Mehl, supervisor for Dakota Co. DOC. Direct by ADA Minser. Witness identifies defendant in the courtroom. Record reflects identification. Cross by Atty Chapman. Witness excused at 1:11 p.m. Defendant would like to testify. Court advises defendant of his right to remain silent. S/T Bryant Killebrew. Direct by Atty Chapman. Cross by ADA Minser. Witness excused. No further evidence by either party. O/R Exhibit #1. Argument by Atty Chapman. Court will grant extradition, deny Writ of Habeas Corpus filed by the defense.
Filed by Atty Kucinski. Requesting a hearing. km

CO: EFV, RPT: Elizabeth Frank, CLERK: E. Ferrill, ADA: Michael Nieskes,  DF:  Bryant Killebrew appeared pro se from jail via video.  Atty Andrea has not spoken with Defendant but has qualified him.  Includes 15CF456 & 15CF510. Defendant has a felony warrant out of Dakota County MN - 15CF456 (has received Govenor's warrant and is pending in front of Branch 4).
